    <item>
      <title>Db - Introduction</title>
      <link>https://www.powerlitepdo.com/docs/1.0.0/db-introduction/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 29 Mar 2024 10:09:39 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.powerlitepdo.com/docs/1.0.0/db-introduction/</guid>
      <description>The Db class is a wrapper around the PHP Data Objects (PDO) extension and serves as a database abstraction layer to provide a simple, consistent interface for interacting with different types of databases.&#xA;It is designed to use procedural methods and is responsible for establishing a connection to the database, executing queries, and returning results. The Db class uses a DriverBase instance for the connection and a QueryBuilder instance for building and executing SQL queries.</description>
    </item>
